\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Introduction
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 \
\
Raw data is rarely perfect. It often contains missing values, noise, and inconsistencies that can affect the performance of machine learning models. 
\f0\b \cf2 Data preprocessing
\f1\b0 \cf2  is a crucial step in data mining that ensures clean and structured data for accurate analysis.\
\

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Steps in Data Preprocessing
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 \
\pard\tqr\tx240\tx400\li400\fi-400\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	1.	
\f0\b Data Cleaning
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tqr\tx500\tx660\li660\fi-660\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	\'95	Handles missing values by 
\f0\b removing them
\f1\b0  or 
\f0\b filling them with estimated values
\f1\b0  (e.g., mean, median).\
	\'95	Identifies and removes 
\f0\b duplicate records
\f1\b0  or 
\f0\b outliers
\f1\b0  that may distort results.\
	\'95	Corrects inconsistent formatting or errors in data entry.\
\pard\tqr\tx240\tx400\li400\fi-400\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	2.	
\f0\b Data Integration
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tqr\tx500\tx660\li660\fi-660\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	\'95	Combines data from multiple sources into a single dataset.\
	\'95	Resolves schema mismatches (e.g., column names might differ across sources).\
\pard\tqr\tx240\tx400\li400\fi-400\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	3.	
\f0\b Data Transformation
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tqr\tx500\tx660\li660\fi-660\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	\'95	Converts data into a suitable format for analysis.\
	\'95	Common techniques:\
\pard\tqr\tx900\tx1060\li1060\fi-1060\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	\'95	
\f0\b Normalization:
\f1\b0  Scaling data values to a standard range (e.g., 0 to 1).\
	\'95	
\f0\b Discretization:
\f1\b0  Converting continuous data into categorical data.\
	\'95	
\f0\b Feature Engineering:
\f1\b0  Creating new features from existing ones to improve model performance.\
\pard\tqr\tx240\tx400\li400\fi-400\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	4.	
\f0\b Data Reduction
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tqr\tx500\tx660\li660\fi-660\sl324\slmult1\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 	\'95	Reduces the volume of data while retaining its important features.\
	\'95	Methods include 
\f0\b Principal Component Analysis (PCA)
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b Feature Selection
\f1\b0  to remove unnecessary attributes.\
\
